The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation will launch on Wednesday a week-long campaign to persuade hawkers to remove their wares from pavements and carriageways. Mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya said the civic authorities, from Thursday next week, will confiscate the wares if they are found on the carriageways or beyond the permissible limit on the pavements. 

 Santana Das, 58, was injured after being hit by a minibus at the Council House Street-Hare Street crossing on Tuesday. She was admitted to Medical College and Hospital and later shifted to a nursing home. The driver has been arrested.

 Babu Das, a conductor, died after falling off the bus and getting run over at the crossing of APC Road and Vivekananda Road on Tuesday. Police said Das, 37, was taken to RG Kar Hospital, where he died. The bus was seized but the driver fled.

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation will undertake micro-tunnelling for repairing underground drinking water and sewage pipes. Finance minister Asim Dasgupta said at Writers Buildings on Tuesday that the mayor has agreed to the proposal submitted to him months ago. 




